<div id="review_3470491734" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3470491734" />
    <a title="DJ Dycus" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4758170-dj-dycus"><img alt="DJ Dycus" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607572719p2/4758170.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3470491734?book_show_action=true">Jul 30, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="DJ Dycus" class="user" itemprop="url" name="DJ Dycus" href="/user/show/4758170-dj-dycus">DJ Dycus</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780679411956" href="/book/show/1071979.I_Am_the_Clay">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4758170-dj-dycus?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4758170-dj-dycus?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4758170-dj-dycus?shelf=bildungsroman">bildungsroman</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4758170-dj-dycus?shelf=american">american</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4758170-dj-dycus?shelf=family">family</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4758170-dj-dycus?shelf=war">war</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4758170-dj-dycus?shelf=military">military</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4758170-dj-dycus?shelf=culture">culture</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4758170-dj-dycus?shelf=self-discovery">self-discovery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4758170-dj-dycus?shelf=communism">communism</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3470491734" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12899851295414667258">A beautiful and powerful story about how vulnerable people help vulnerable people when they&apos;re trapped between the cogs of war.<br/><br/>This story is probably closest to <i>The Book of Lights</i>, in that both stories take place during the Korean War -- but it is unlike anything else that I have read by him. The entire story focuses upon an elderly couple who stumble upon an injured boy, all of whom are displaced by war. I kept expecting Potok to shift to another storyline, like the soldiers in the war, but the</span>
  <span id="freeText12899851295414667258" style="display:none">A beautiful and powerful story about how vulnerable people help vulnerable people when they're trapped between the cogs of war.<br /><br />This story is probably closest to <i>The Book of Lights</i>, in that both stories take place during the Korean War -- but it is unlike anything else that I have read by him. The entire story focuses upon an elderly couple who stumble upon an injured boy, all of whom are displaced by war. I kept expecting Potok to shift to another storyline, like the soldiers in the war, but the story is all about these Korean peasants.<br /><br />Another pleasant element was the structure of the book. The settings go B, C, D, E, D, C, B, and then A. This was a surprise; I wasn't expecting the story to move beyond B, which is where the story opens.<br /><br />This book is both powerful as well as poignant. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12899851295414667258" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


