<span id="freeTextContainer17674132678662393907">Probably 3.5 for me. The novel follows a stream of consciousness, but drifts between the three main characters with no warning which can make it difficult to follow at times. Potok vividly describes the struggles of being a refugee and helps to paint a picture of life during the Korean war. It wasn&apos;t the most enjoyable book to read, but I think it was worthwhile.</span>
  <span id="freeText17674132678662393907" style="display:none">Probably 3.5 for me. The novel follows a stream of consciousness, but drifts between the three main characters with no warning which can make it difficult to follow at times. Potok vividly describes the struggles of being a refugee and helps to paint a picture of life during the Korean war. It wasn't the most enjoyable book to read, but I think it was worthwhile.</span>
