<div id="review_3385636136" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3385636136" />
    <a title="Angie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5006924-angie"><img alt="Angie" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3385636136?book_show_action=true">Jun 10, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Angie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Angie" href="/user/show/5006924-angie">Angie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5006924-angie?shelf=history">history</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3385636136" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14384803994179744993">Glad that I read it for the eye-opening historical understanding; however, I was disappointed in a few things, and it is for the most part, a sad read. At times it seemed slow...but then again...it does make one understand some of what people endured. I think the most troublesome to me about this book is it&apos;s very occasional references of sexual nature, and how they were depicted, that I felt were unnecessary and distracted from the main points of the story. I wonder why the author felt the need</span>
  <span id="freeText14384803994179744993" style="display:none">Glad that I read it for the eye-opening historical understanding; however, I was disappointed in a few things, and it is for the most part, a sad read. At times it seemed slow...but then again...it does make one understand some of what people endured. I think the most troublesome to me about this book is it's very occasional references of sexual nature, and how they were depicted, that I felt were unnecessary and distracted from the main points of the story. I wonder why the author felt the need to include them even? I also found the repetitive reference to the smoke troubling to my heart...but, again, that certainly did bring that reality to one's understanding...troubling as it is. :( This is NOT a joyful read, but rather one that hopefully rises empathy for the people who lived similar experiences.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14384803994179744993" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


